@database AreaClass
@index "Classes.guide/Main"

@Node Main "RxMUI - Area Class"


Area class    @{"Index" link "Classes.guide/Main"} @{"Super" link "NotifyClass.guide/Main"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  Area class objects are not usefull at all, but Area class
  attribute and methods may be used with any of its subclasses.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Background@{fg text}
  S IS
  One of:
     o None
     o WindowBack
     o RequesterBack
     o ButtonBack
     o ListBack
     o TextBack
     o PropBack
     o PopupBack
     o RegisterBack
     o GroupBack
     o SliderBack
     o PageBack
     o ReadListBack
     o Background
     o Shadow
     o Shine
     o Fill
     o ShadowBack
     o ShadowFill
     o ShadowShine
     o FillBack
     o FillShine
     o ShineBack
     o FillBack2
     o HShineBack
     o HShadowBack
     o HShineShine
     o HShadowShadow
     o MarkShine
     o MarkHalfShine
     o MarkBackground

  @{fg shine}BottomEdge@{fg text}
  N G

  @{fg shine}ContextMenu@{fg text}
  S IS
  This is a Menustrip object that is used as context menu. The
  same Menustrip may be used as context menu for many objects;
  the only limitation is that they must be in the same window.
  RxMUI does not check for that! Please be careful.

  @{fg shine}ControlChar@{fg text}
  C ISG
  A char to use as key for the Object. Note that not all the
  classes react to control chars.

  @{fg shine}CycleChain@{fg text}
  N ISG

  @{fg shine}Disabled@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}Draggable@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{fg shine}Dropable@{fg text}
  B ISG

  @{fg shine}EBackground@{fg text}
  M I
  It accepts the same value as Background plus the same format of
  Image class @{"Spec" LINK "ImageClass.guide/Main"} attribute (e.g. "5:images/back.gif"). Remember
  that to set the background of a window you have to simply set
  the background of its root (Contents) object.

  @{fg shine}FillArea@{fg text}
  B IS
  Useless in RxMUI.

  @{fg shine}FixHeight@{fg text}
  N I

  @{fg shine}FixHeightTxt@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}FixWidth@{fg text}
  N I

  @{fg shine}FixWidthTxt@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}Font@{fg text}
  S IS
  One of:
     o Inherit
     o Normal
     o List
     o Tiny
     o Fixed
     o Title
     o Big
     o Button

  @{fg shine}Frame@{fg text}
  S I
  One of:
     o None
     o Button
     o ImageButton
     o Text
     o String
     o ReadList
     o InputList
     o Prop
     o Gauge
     o Group
     o Popup
     o Virtual
     o Slider

  @{fg shine}FramePhantomHoriz@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}FrameTitle@{fg text}
  S I

  @{fg shine}Height@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}HorizDisappear@{fg text}
  N ISG

  @{fg shine}HorizWeight@{fg text}
  N ISG

  @{fg shine}InnerBottom@{fg text}
  N IG

  @{fg shine}InnerLeft@{fg text}
  N IG

  @{fg shine}InnerRight@{fg text}
  N IG

  @{fg shine}InnerTop@{fg text}
  N IG

  @{fg shine}InputMode@{fg text}
  S I One of:
     o None
     o RelVerify
     o Immediate
     o Toggle

  @{fg shine}LeftEdge@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}MaxHeight@{fg text}
  N I

  @{fg shine}MaxWidth@{fg text}
  N I

  @{fg shine}Pressed@{fg text}
  B GN

  @{fg shine}RightEdge@{fg text}
  N G

  @{fg shine}Selected@{fg text}
  B ISGN

  @{fg shine}ShortHelp@{fg text}
  S ISG

  @{fg shine}ShowMe@{fg text}
  B ISGN
  You should use Add/Remove rather than this.

  @{fg shine}ShowSelState@{fg text}
  B I

  @{fg shine}Timer@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}TopEdge@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{fg shine}VertDisappear@{fg text}
  N ISGN

  @{fg shine}VertWeight@{fg text}
  N ISG

  @{fg shine}Weight@{fg text}
  N IS

  @{fg shine}Width@{fg text}
  N GN

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  None defined

@EndNode
